# FILE ORGANIZATION RULES [CRITICAL - ABSOLUTE REQUIREMENT]

31. [CRITICAL] ALL new files MUST be automatically organized into appropriate directories:
    
    **Directory Structure:**
    - `.cursor/agents/` - Cursor subagent specs (`.md`); **canonical agent roles in this workspace**
    - `config/` - Configuration files (.json, .yaml, .properties, specs, templates)
    - `docs/` - Documentation files (.md, .txt, .rst)
    - `Cursor-Project/User story/` - User stories, flows, and related documentation files (.txt, .drawio, .md) - **MANDATORY location for ALL story/flow files**
    - `reports/` - Report files (.md) under **`Cursor-Project/reports/`** → **`Chat reports/`**, **`HandsOff reports/`**, **`Feedback/`**, each with **`YYYY/<english-month>/<DD>/`** before the filename — see **`Cursor-Project/reports/README.md`**
    - `test_cases/` - **Test cases (MANDATORY layout)** – `Backend/` for TC-BE-N; `Frontend/` for TC-FE-N **only when TC-FRONTEND-ASK.0 = Yes**. Same topic name per folder when both are generated. See `.cursor/rules/workspace/test_cases_structure.mdc`. Path: `Cursor-Project/test_cases/`
    - `Phoenix/` - Phoenix Java project files (git submodules, READ-ONLY)
    
    **Process:**
    1. Identify file type and match to directory
    2. Place in correct directory (create subdirectories if needed)
    3. For reports: pick area + `YYYY/<english-month>/<DD>` per **`Cursor-Project/reports/README.md`** and Rule 0.6
    4. Use descriptive names following existing patterns
    
    **Special Rule for Stories and Flows:**
    - When user requests creation of a story or flow file, it MUST be saved in `Cursor-Project/User story/` directory
    - This applies to: user stories, flow diagrams, story documentation, flow documentation
    - File types: .txt, .drawio, .md, or any format related to stories/flows
    
    **CRITICAL: User Stories MUST be written in English:**
    - ALL user stories, acceptance criteria, business rules, and technical documentation within story files MUST be written in English
    - This applies to ALL story files in `Cursor-Project/User story/` directory
    - Only code examples, file paths, and technical identifiers may contain non-English text
    - Violation is a **MUST**
    
    **Examples:**
    - ✅ `.cursor/agents/bug-validator.md` (Cursor subagent — NOT Python in root)
    - ✅ `Cursor-Project/reports/Chat reports/2026/april/12/Summary_1430.md` (layout per `reports/README.md`; `12` = real save day)
    - ❌ `reports/AgentReport.md` in workspace root → Should be under `Cursor-Project/reports/<area>/YYYY/<english-month>/<DD>/` per **`Cursor-Project/reports/README.md`**
    - ✅ `Cursor-Project/User story/MY_USER_STORY.txt` (story files MUST go here)
    - ✅ `Cursor-Project/User story/MY_FLOW_DIAGRAM.drawio` (flow files MUST go here)
    - ❌ `MY_STORY.txt` in root → Should be `Cursor-Project/User story/MY_STORY.txt`
   - ✅ `Cursor-Project/test_cases/Backend/Invoice_cancellation.md` + `Cursor-Project/test_cases/Frontend/Invoice_cancellation.md` (test cases – two-folder layout; see test_cases_structure.mdc)
   - ✅ `Cursor-Project/test_cases/Backend/Product_contract_create.md` + `Cursor-Project/test_cases/Frontend/Product_contract_create.md`
    - ✅ `Cursor-Project/generated_test_cases/Object/customer/Create.md` (legacy hierarchical test cases)
    
    Violation is a **MUST**.
